2 E. Transmission and disposition of original challenges, duplicate voters'
3 affidavits, and address confirmation notices. (1) At the opening of the voting
4 machines, the sealed precinct registers shall be immediately returned to the registrar
5 of voters. Upon receipt of the sealed precinct registers, the registrar shall remove any
6 attached original record of challenges of voters made during the election, any
7 precinct register correction affidavits, any voter identification affidavits made
8 pursuant to R.S. 18:562, any address confirmation notices, any voter assistance
9 forms, any certificates, any copies of disability documentation, and any completed
10 voter registration applications.
11 (2) The registrar shall utilize the procedures set forth in Part V of Chapter 4
12 of this Code to determine the validity of the registration of each challenged voter
13 who did not submit an address confirmation notice. In any instance where an address
14 confirmation notice was received that stated an address different from the address
15 on file in the registrar's office for a registrant, the registrar shall change the
16 registrant's address to the address on the address confirmation notice if the change
17 of address is in the parish; transfer the registrant's registration to another parish if the
18 address on the address confirmation notice is in another parish; or cancel the
19 registration if the address on the address confirmation notice is in another state. If an
20 address confirmation notice was received that affirmed the address on file in the
21 registrar's office, the registrar shall reinstate the registrant to the official list of voters
22 if the registrant appears on the inactive list of voters. If the address confirmation
23 notice was a result of a valid challenge, the registrar shall so inform the district
24 attorney and shall transmit to him the address confirmation notice of that person.
25 (3) The registrar also shall proceed to determine if each voter submitting a
26 voter identification affidavit made pursuant to R.S. 18:562 attesting that he is a
27 qualified registered voter is in fact a registered voter qualified to vote in the election
28 by comparing the information provided by the voter with the information on file in
29 the registrar's office and by reasonably comparing the signature on the affidavit with
30 any signature on file for the voter in the registrar's office. If the registrar determines
